<br>
No.  That is, at least in part, because it would be unenforceable.<br>
<br>
&quot;However, there is an ignore command for a reason, and I would suggest you use it.&quot;<br>
<br>
I do.  But I can't ignore 500 people.  I can't ignore a gradual shift in the tone of the server I started playing EQ in order to play on.<br>
<br>
&quot;It isn't up to you or me to decide how others should play the game. You might think the server would be better if everyone acted the way you want them to, but in truth would it be?&quot;<br>
<br>
In the past I've used the analogy of a square dancing club.  A square dancing club is set up for people who like square dancing.  If you don't like square dancing there are MANY other clubs out there.  If you find there are other reasons you want to go to a square dancing club (the drinks are cheap, it's non-smoking, your friends go there) no one should kick you out.  BUT you also shouldn't loudly deride square dancing, try to start a mosh pit or attempt to hijack the dj booth to play Lawrence Welk.  That's rude and it threatens the very esistence of the club you want to go to because if the regulars give up on going to that club (or even clubs in general) then it's going to either close or change in such a way that it is likely to lose all the things you LIKE as well as the square dancing.<br>
<br>
I hate square dancing.<br>
<br>
&quot;In short, people that get upset because someone say &quot;sow plz&quot; are no less pathetic than the person who asks that on a RP preferred server.&quot;<br>
<br>
It seems a trivial thing to get upset over, I'll agree.  I don't get upset.  I do get annoyed a bit at having someone force their game style onto me when, I feel, I am trying to preserve the spirit the server was designed in.  There are PLENTY of other servers.  If people can't make any effort to RP then why don't they petition Verant to start a non-RP server with all the unique rules FV still managed to cling to and transfer there?  The outflux from FV might close it and then this argument would, at least, be settled once and for all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BakoFV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Ladies Leezard</span><br>  Posts: 323<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 1:57:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1135.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SERIOUS MESSAGE FOR FIRE AND FURY MEMBERS</span><hr size=1> Thunder Thunder Thunder, Thunder Cats! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Political Piggies</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 2:03:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1135.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Do I have todrag out the square dancing analogy AGAIN?</span><hr size=1> Viren, if I didn't bother you and all was ship-shape in FaF land, you wouldn't have replied <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www